138static void translate_error_to_exception(void)
139{
140 PyErr_SetString(opencv_error, cvErrorStr(cvGetErrStatus()));
141 cvSetErrStatus(0);
142}
143
144#define ERRCHK do { if (cvGetErrStatus() != 0) { translate_error_to_exception(); return 0; } } while (0)
145#define ERRWRAPN(F, N) \
146 do { \
147 try \
148 { \
149 F; \
150 } \
151 catch (const cv::Exception &e) \
152 { \
153 PyErr_SetString(opencv_error, e.err.c_str()); \
154 return N; \
155 } \
156 ERRCHK; \
157 } while(0)
158#define ERRWRAP(F) ERRWRAPN(F, NULL) // for most functions, exception -> NULL return

164static PyObject *PyObject_FromCvScalar(CvScalar s, int type)
165{
166 int i, spe = CV_MAT_CN(type);
167 PyObject *r;
168 if (spe > 1) {
169 r = PyTuple_New(spe);
170 for (i = 0; i < spe; i++)
171 PyTuple_SET_ITEM(r, i, PyFloat_FromDouble(s.val[i]));
172 } else {
173 r = PyFloat_FromDouble(s.val[0]);
174 }
175 return r;
176}

181// o is a Python string or buffer object. Return its size.
182
183static Py_ssize_t what_size(PyObject *o)
184{
185 void *buffer;
186 Py_ssize_t buffer_len;
187
188 if (PyString_Check(o)) {
189 return PyString_Size(o);
190 } else if (PyObject_AsWriteBuffer(o, &buffer, &buffer_len) == 0) {
191 return buffer_len;
192 } else {
193 assert(0); // argument must be string or buffer.
194 return 0;
195 }
196}

249static PyObject *iplimage_tostring(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
250{
251 IplImage *i=0;
252 if (!convert_to_IplImage(self, &i, "self"))
253 return NULL;
254 if (i == NULL)
255 return NULL;
256 cv::Mat img(i);
257 size_t esz = img.elemSize();
258 int nrows = img.rows, ncols = img.cols;
259
260 if( !img.isContinuous() )
261 img = img.clone();
262 return PyString_FromStringAndSize((char*)img.data, (Py_ssize_t)(esz*nrows*ncols));
263}

346static PyObject *cvmat_repr(PyObject *self)
347{
348 CvMat *m = ((cvmat_t*)self)->a;
349 char str[1000];
350 sprintf(str, "<cvmat(");
351 char *d = str + strlen(str);
352 sprintf(d, "type=%08x ", m->type);
353 d += strlen(d);
354 switch (CV_MAT_DEPTH(m->type)) {
355 case CV_8U: strcpy(d, "8U"); break;
356 case CV_8S: strcpy(d, "8S"); break;
357 case CV_16U: strcpy(d, "16U"); break;
358 case CV_16S: strcpy(d, "16S"); break;
359 case CV_32S: strcpy(d, "32S"); break;
360 case CV_32F: strcpy(d, "32F"); break;
361 case CV_64F: strcpy(d, "64F"); break;
362 }
363 d += strlen(d);
364 sprintf(d, "C%d ", CV_MAT_CN(m->type));
365 d += strlen(d);
366 sprintf(d, "rows=%d ", m->rows);
367 d += strlen(d);
368 sprintf(d, "cols=%d ", m->cols);
369 d += strlen(d);
370 sprintf(d, "step=%d ", m->step);
371 d += strlen(d);
372 sprintf(d, ")>");
373 return PyString_FromString(str);
374}

376static PyObject *cvmat_tostring(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
377{
378 CvMat *m;
379 if (!convert_to_CvMat(self, &m, "self"))
380 return NULL;
381
382 int bps; // bytes per sample
383
384 switch (CV_MAT_DEPTH(m->type)) {
385 case CV_8U:
386 case CV_8S:
387 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 1;
388 break;
389 case CV_16U:
390 case CV_16S:
391 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 2;
392 break;
393 case CV_32S:
394 case CV_32F:
395 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 4;
396 break;
397 case CV_64F:
398 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 8;
399 break;
400 default:
401 failmsg("Unrecognized depth %d", CV_MAT_DEPTH(m->type));
402 return (PyObject*)0;
403 }
404
405 int bpl = m->cols * bps; // bytes per line
406 cvmat_t *pc = (cvmat_t*)self;
407 if (PyString_Check(pc->data) && bpl == m->step && pc->offset == 0 && ((bpl * m->rows) == what_size(pc->data))) {
408 Py_INCREF(pc->data);
409 return pc->data;
410 } else {
411 int l = bpl * m->rows;
412 char *s = new char[l];
413 int y;
414 for (y = 0; y < m->rows; y++) {
415 memcpy(s + y * bpl, m->data.ptr + y * m->step, bpl);
416 }
417 PyObject *r = PyString_FromStringAndSize(s, l);
418 delete[] s;
419 return r;
420 }
421}

457// A PyArrayInterface, with an associated python object that should be DECREF'ed on release
458struct arrayTrack {
459 PyArrayInterface s;
460 PyObject *o;
461};
462
463static void arrayTrackDtor(void *p)
464{
465 struct arrayTrack *at = (struct arrayTrack *)p;
466 delete[] at->s.shape;
467 delete[] at->s.strides;
468 if (at->s.descr)
469 Py_DECREF(at->s.descr);
470 Py_DECREF(at->o);
471}
472
473// Fill in fields of PyArrayInterface s using mtype. This code is common
474// to cvmat and cvmatnd
475
476static void arrayinterface_common(PyArrayInterface *s, int mtype)
477{
478 s->two = 2;
479
480 switch (CV_MAT_DEPTH(mtype)) {
481 case CV_8U:
482 s->typekind = 'u';
483 s->itemsize = 1;
484 break;
485 case CV_8S:
486 s->typekind = 'i';
487 s->itemsize = 1;
488 break;
489 case CV_16U:
490 s->typekind = 'u';
491 s->itemsize = 2;
492 break;
493 case CV_16S:
494 s->typekind = 'i';
495 s->itemsize = 2;
496 break;
497 case CV_32S:
498 s->typekind = 'i';
499 s->itemsize = 4;
500 break;
501 case CV_32F:
502 s->typekind = 'f';
503 s->itemsize = 4;
504 break;
505 case CV_64F:
506 s->typekind = 'f';
507 s->itemsize = 8;
508 break;
509 default:
510 assert(0);
511 }
512
513#ifdef NPY_1_7_API_VERSION
514 s->flags = NPY_ARRAY_WRITEABLE | NPY_ARRAY_NOTSWAPPED;
515#else
516 s->flags = NPY_WRITEABLE | NPY_NOTSWAPPED;
517#endif
518}
519
520static PyObject *cvmat_array_struct(cvmat_t *cva)
521{
522 CvMat *m;
523 convert_to_CvMat((PyObject *)cva, &m, "");
524
525 arrayTrack *at = new arrayTrack;
526 PyArrayInterface *s = &at->s;
527
528 at->o = cva->data;
529 Py_INCREF(at->o);
530
531 arrayinterface_common(s, m->type);
532
533 if (CV_MAT_CN(m->type) == 1) {
534 s->nd = 2;
535 s->shape = new npy_intp[2];
536 s->shape[0] = m->rows;
537 s->shape[1] = m->cols;
538 s->strides = new npy_intp[2];
539 s->strides[0] = m->step;
540 s->strides[1] = s->itemsize;
541 } else {
542 s->nd = 3;
543 s->shape = new npy_intp[3];
544 s->shape[0] = m->rows;
545 s->shape[1] = m->cols;
546 s->shape[2] = CV_MAT_CN(m->type);
547 s->strides = new npy_intp[3];
548 s->strides[0] = m->step;
549 s->strides[1] = s->itemsize * CV_MAT_CN(m->type);
550 s->strides[2] = s->itemsize;
551 }
552 s->data = (void*)(m->data.ptr);
553 s->descr = PyList_New(1);
554 char typestr[10];
555 sprintf(typestr, "<%c%d", s->typekind, s->itemsize);
556 PyList_SetItem(s->descr, 0, Py_BuildValue("(ss)", "x", typestr));
557
558 return PyCObject_FromVoidPtr(s, arrayTrackDtor);
559}
560
561static PyObject *cvmatnd_array_struct(cvmatnd_t *cva)
562{
563 CvMatND *m = 0;
564 convert_to_CvMatND((PyObject *)cva, &m, "");
565
566 arrayTrack *at = new arrayTrack;
567 PyArrayInterface *s = &at->s;
568
569 at->o = cva->data;
570 Py_INCREF(at->o);
571
572 arrayinterface_common(s, m->type);
573
574 int i;
575 if (CV_MAT_CN(m->type) == 1) {
576 s->nd = m->dims;
577 s->shape = new npy_intp[s->nd];
578 for (i = 0; i < s->nd; i++)
579 s->shape[i] = m->dim[i].size;
580 s->strides = new npy_intp[s->nd];
581 for (i = 0; i < (s->nd - 1); i++)
582 s->strides[i] = m->dim[i].step;
583 s->strides[s->nd - 1] = s->itemsize;
584 } else {
585 s->nd = m->dims + 1;
586 s->shape = new npy_intp[s->nd];
587 for (i = 0; i < (s->nd - 1); i++)
588 s->shape[i] = m->dim[i].size;
589 s->shape[s->nd - 1] = CV_MAT_CN(m->type);
590
591 s->strides = new npy_intp[s->nd];
592 for (i = 0; i < (s->nd - 2); i++)
593 s->strides[i] = m->dim[i].step;
594 s->strides[s->nd - 2] = s->itemsize * CV_MAT_CN(m->type);
595 s->strides[s->nd - 1] = s->itemsize;
596 }
597 s->data = (void*)(m->data.ptr);
598 s->descr = PyList_New(1);
599 char typestr[10];
600 sprintf(typestr, "<%c%d", s->typekind, s->itemsize);
601 PyList_SetItem(s->descr, 0, Py_BuildValue("(ss)", "x", typestr));
602
603 return PyCObject_FromVoidPtr(s, arrayTrackDtor);
604}

680static size_t cvmatnd_size(CvMatND *m)
681{
682 int bps = 1;
683 switch (CV_MAT_DEPTH(m->type)) {
684 case CV_8U:
685 case CV_8S:
686 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 1;
687 break;
688 case CV_16U:
689 case CV_16S:
690 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 2;
691 break;
692 case CV_32S:
693 case CV_32F:
694 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 4;
695 break;
696 case CV_64F:
697 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 8;
698 break;
699 default:
700 assert(0);
701 }
702 size_t l = bps;
703 for (int d = 0; d < m->dims; d++) {
704 l *= m->dim[d].size;
705 }
706 return l;
707}
708
709static PyObject *cvmatnd_tostring(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
710{
711 CvMatND *m = 0;
712 if (!convert_to_CvMatND(self, &m, "self"))
713 return NULL;
714
715 int bps;
716 switch (CV_MAT_DEPTH(m->type)) {
717 case CV_8U:
718 case CV_8S:
719 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 1;
720 break;
721 case CV_16U:
722 case CV_16S:
723 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 2;
724 break;
725 case CV_32S:
726 case CV_32F:
727 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 4;
728 break;
729 case CV_64F:
730 bps = CV_MAT_CN(m->type) * 8;
731 break;
732 default:
733 return failmsg("Unrecognised depth %d", CV_MAT_DEPTH(m->type)), (PyObject*)0;
734 }
735
736 int d, l = bps;
737 for (d = 0; d < m->dims; d++) {
738 l *= m->dim[d].size;
739 }
740 int i[CV_MAX_DIM];
741 for (d = 0; d < m->dims; d++) {
742 i[d] = 0;
743 }
744 int rowsize = m->dim[m->dims-1].size * bps;
745 char *s = new char[l];
746 char *ps = s;
747
748 int finished = 0;
749 while (!finished) {
750 memcpy(ps, cvPtrND(m, i), rowsize);
751 ps += rowsize;
752 for (d = m->dims - 2; 0 <= d; d--) {
753 if (++i[d] < cvGetDimSize(m, d)) {
754 break;
755 } else {
756 i[d] = 0;
757 }
758 }
759 if (d < 0)
760 finished = 1;
761 }
762
763 return PyString_FromStringAndSize(s, ps - s);
764}
765

769 {NULL, NULL}
770};

891/* memtrack */
892
893/* Motivation for memtrack is when the storage for a Mat is an array or buffer
894object. By setting 'data' to be a memtrack, can deallocate the storage at
895object destruction.
896
897For array objects, 'backing' is the actual storage object. memtrack holds the reference,
898then DECREF's it at dealloc.
899
900For MatND's, we need to cvDecRefData() on release, and this is what field 'backingmat' is for.
901
902If freeptr is true, then a straight cvFree() of ptr happens.
903
904*/
905
906
907static void memtrack_dealloc(PyObject *self)
908{
909 memtrack_t *pi = (memtrack_t*)self;
910 if (pi->backing)
911 Py_DECREF(pi->backing);
912 if (pi->backingmat)
913 cvDecRefData(pi->backingmat);
914 if (pi->freeptr)
915 cvFree(&pi->ptr);
916 PyObject_Del(self);
917}
918

921 0, /*size*/
922 OLD_MODULESTR".memtrack", /*name*/

924};

930}

1086{
1087 cvseq_t *ps = (cvseq_t*)o;
1088 if (ps->a == NULL)
1089 return (Py_ssize_t)0;
1090 else

1094static PyObject* cvseq_seq_getitem(PyObject *o, Py_ssize_t i)
1095{
1096 cvseq_t *ps = (cvseq_t*)o;
1097 CvPoint *pt;
1098 struct pointpair{
1099 CvPoint a, b;
1100 } *pp;
1101 CvPoint2D32f *pt2;
1102 CvPoint3D32f *pt3;
1103
1104 if (i < cvseq_seq_length(o)) {
1105 switch (CV_SEQ_ELTYPE(ps->a)) {
1106
1107 case CV_SEQ_ELTYPE_POINT:
1108 pt = CV_GET_SEQ_ELEM(CvPoint, ps->a, (int)i);
1109 return Py_BuildValue("ii", pt->x, pt->y);
1110
1111 case CV_SEQ_ELTYPE_GENERIC:
1112 switch (ps->a->elem_size) {
1113 case sizeof(CvQuadEdge2D):
1114 {
1115 cvsubdiv2dedge_t *r = PyObject_NEW(cvsubdiv2dedge_t, &cvsubdiv2dedge_Type);
1116 r->a = (CvSubdiv2DEdge)CV_GET_SEQ_ELEM(CvQuadEdge2D, ps->a, (int)i);
1117 r->container = ps->container;
1118 Py_INCREF(r->container);
1119 return (PyObject*)r;
1120 }
1121 case sizeof(CvConnectedComp):
1122 {
1123 CvConnectedComp *cc = CV_GET_SEQ_ELEM(CvConnectedComp, ps->a, (int)i);
1124 return FROM_CvConnectedComp(*cc);
1125 }
1126 default:
1127 printf("seq elem size is %d\n", ps->a->elem_size);
1128 printf("KIND %d\n", CV_SEQ_KIND(ps->a));
1129 assert(0);
1130 }
1131 return PyInt_FromLong(*CV_GET_SEQ_ELEM(unsigned char, ps->a, (int)i));
1132
1133 case CV_SEQ_ELTYPE_PTR:
1134 case CV_SEQ_ELTYPE_INDEX:
1135 return PyInt_FromLong(*CV_GET_SEQ_ELEM(int, ps->a, (int)i));
1136
1137 case CV_32SC4:
1138 pp = CV_GET_SEQ_ELEM(pointpair, ps->a, (int)i);
1139 return Py_BuildValue("(ii),(ii)", pp->a.x, pp->a.y, pp->b.x, pp->b.y);
1140
1141 case CV_32FC2:
1142 pt2 = CV_GET_SEQ_ELEM(CvPoint2D32f, ps->a, (int)i);
1143 return Py_BuildValue("ff", pt2->x, pt2->y);
1144
1145 case CV_SEQ_ELTYPE_POINT3D:
1146 pt3 = CV_GET_SEQ_ELEM(CvPoint3D32f, ps->a, (int)i);
1147 return Py_BuildValue("fff", pt3->x, pt3->y, pt3->z);
1148
1149 default:
1150 printf("Unknown element type %08x\n", CV_SEQ_ELTYPE(ps->a));
1151 assert(0);
1152 return NULL;
1153 }
1154 } else
1155 return NULL;
1156}
1157
1158static PyObject* cvseq_map_getitem(PyObject *o, PyObject *item)
1159{
1160 if (PyInt_Check(item)) {
1161 int i = (int)PyInt_AS_LONG(item);
1162 if (i < 0)
1163 i += (int)cvseq_seq_length(o);
1164 return cvseq_seq_getitem(o, i);
1165 } else if (!!PySlice_Check(item)) {
1166 Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slicelength, cur, i;
1167 PyObject* result;
1168
1169 if (PySlice_GetIndicesEx((PySliceObject*)item, cvseq_seq_length(o),
1170 &start, &stop, &step, &slicelength) < 0) {
1171 return NULL;
1172 }
1173
1174 if (slicelength <= 0) {
1175 return PyList_New(0);
1176 } else {
1177 result = PyList_New(slicelength);
1178 if (!result) return NULL;
1179
1180 for (cur = start, i = 0; i < slicelength;
1181 cur += step, i++) {
1182 PyList_SET_ITEM(result, i, cvseq_seq_getitem(o, cur));
1183 }
1184
1185 return result;
1186 }
1187 } else {
1188 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "CvSeq indices must be integers");
1189 return NULL;
1190 }
1191}

1411static int convert_to_CvScalar(PyObject *o, CvScalar *s, const char *name = "no_name")
1412{
1413 if (PySequence_Check(o)) {
1414 PyObject *fi = PySequence_Fast(o, name);
1415 if (fi == NULL)
1416 return 0;
1417 if (4 < PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi))
1418 return failmsg("CvScalar value for argument '%s' is longer than 4", name);
1419 for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi); i++) {
1420 PyObject *item = PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(fi, i);
1421 if (PyFloat_Check(item) || PyInt_Check(item)) {
1422 s->val[i] = PyFloat_AsDouble(item);
1423 } else {
1424 return failmsg("CvScalar value for argument '%s' is not numeric", name);
1425 }
1426 }
1427 Py_DECREF(fi);
1428 } else {
1429 if (PyFloat_Check(o) || PyInt_Check(o)) {
1430 s->val[0] = PyFloat_AsDouble(o);
1431 } else {
1432 return failmsg("CvScalar value for argument '%s' is not numeric", name);
1433 }
1434 }
1435 return 1;
1436}

1559static int convert_to_IplImage(PyObject *o, IplImage **dst, const char *name)
1560{
1561 iplimage_t *ipl = (iplimage_t*)o;
1562 void *buffer;
1563 Py_ssize_t buffer_len;
1564
1565 if (!is_iplimage(o)) {
1566 return failmsg("Argument '%s' must be IplImage", name);
1567 } else if (PyString_Check(ipl->data)) {
1568 cvSetData(ipl->a, PyString_AsString(ipl->data) + ipl->offset, ipl->a->widthStep);
1569 assert(cvGetErrStatus() == 0);
1570 *dst = ipl->a;
1571 return 1;
1572 } else if (ipl->data && PyObject_AsWriteBuffer(ipl->data, &buffer, &buffer_len) == 0) {
1573 cvSetData(ipl->a, (void*)((char*)buffer + ipl->offset), ipl->a->widthStep);
1574 assert(cvGetErrStatus() == 0);
1575 *dst = ipl->a;
1576 return 1;
1577 } else {
1578 return failmsg("IplImage argument '%s' has no data", name);
1579 }
1580}

1582static int convert_to_CvMat(PyObject *o, CvMat **dst, const char *name)
1583{
1584 cvmat_t *m = (cvmat_t*)o;
1585 void *buffer;
1586 Py_ssize_t buffer_len;
1587
1588 if (!is_cvmat(o)) {
1589//#if !PYTHON_USE_NUMPY
1590 return failmsg("Argument '%s' must be CvMat. Use fromarray() to convert numpy arrays to CvMat", name);
1591/*#else
1592 PyObject *asmat = fromarray(o, 0);
1593 if (asmat == NULL)
1594 return failmsg("Argument '%s' must be CvMat", name);
1595 // now have the array obect as a cvmat, can use regular conversion
1596 return convert_to_CvMat(asmat, dst, name);
1597#endif*/
1598 } else {
1599 m->a->refcount = NULL;
1600 if (m->data && PyString_Check(m->data)) {
1601 assert(cvGetErrStatus() == 0);
1602 char *ptr = PyString_AsString(m->data) + m->offset;
1603 cvSetData(m->a, ptr, m->a->step);
1604 assert(cvGetErrStatus() == 0);
1605 *dst = m->a;
1606 return 1;
1607 } else if (m->data && PyObject_AsWriteBuffer(m->data, &buffer, &buffer_len) == 0) {
1608 cvSetData(m->a, (void*)((char*)buffer + m->offset), m->a->step);
1609 assert(cvGetErrStatus() == 0);
1610 *dst = m->a;
1611 return 1;
1612 } else if (m->data && m->a->data.ptr){
1613 *dst = m->a;
1614 return 1;
1615 }
1616 else {
1617 return failmsg("CvMat argument '%s' has no data", name);
1618 }
1619 }
1620}

1703class cvarrseq {
1704public:
1705 union {
1706 CvSeq *seq;
1707 CvArr *mat;
1708 };
1709 int freemat;
1710 cvarrseq() {
1711 freemat = false;
1712 }
1713 ~cvarrseq() {
1714 if (freemat) {
1715 cvReleaseMat((CvMat**)&mat);
1716 }
1717 }
1718};
1719
1720static int is_convertible_to_mat(PyObject *o)
1721{
1722#if PYTHON_USE_NUMPY
1723 if (PyObject_HasAttrString(o, "__array_struct__")) {
1724 PyObject *ao = PyObject_GetAttrString(o, "__array_struct__");
1725 if (ao != NULL &&
1726 PyCObject_Check(ao) &&
1727 ((PyArrayInterface*)PyCObject_AsVoidPtr(ao))->two == 2) {
1728 return 1;
1729 }
1730 }
1731#endif
1732 return is_iplimage(o) && is_cvmat(o) && is_cvmatnd(o);
1733}
1734
1735static int convert_to_cvarrseq(PyObject *o, cvarrseq *dst, const char *name = "no_name")
1736{
1737 if (PyType_IsSubtype(o->ob_type, &cvseq_Type)) {
1738 return convert_to_CvSeq(o, &(dst->seq), name);
1739 } else if (is_convertible_to_mat(o)) {
1740 int r = convert_to_CvArr(o, &(dst->mat), name);
1741 return r;
1742 } else if (PySequence_Check(o)) {
1743 PyObject *fi = PySequence_Fast(o, name);
1744 if (fi == NULL)
1745 return 0;
1746 Py_ssize_t size = -1;
1747 // Make a pass through the sequence, checking that each element is
1748 // a sequence and that they are all the same size
1749 for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi); i++) {
1750 PyObject *e = PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(fi, i);
1751
1752 if (!PySequence_Check(e))
1753 return failmsg("Sequence '%s' must contain sequences", name);
1754 if (i == 0)
1755 size = (int)PySequence_Size(e);
1756 else if (size != PySequence_Size(e))
1757 return failmsg("All elements of sequence '%s' must be same size", name);
1758 }
1759 assert(size != -1);
1760 CvMat *mt = cvCreateMat((int)PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi), 1, CV_32SC((int)size));
1761 dst->freemat = true; // dealloc this mat when done
1762 for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi); i++) {
1763 PyObject *e = PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(fi, i);
1764 PyObject *fe = PySequence_Fast(e, name);
1765 assert(fe != NULL);
1766 int *pdst = (int*)cvPtr2D(mt, (int)i, 0);
1767 for (Py_ssize_t j = 0; j < size; j++) {
1768 PyObject *num = PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(fe, j);
1769 if (!PyNumber_Check(num)) {
1770 return failmsg("Sequence must contain numbers", name);
1771 }
1772 *pdst++ = PyInt_AsLong(num);
1773 }
1774 Py_DECREF(fe);
1775 }
1776 Py_DECREF(fi);
1777 dst->mat = mt;
1778 return 1;
1779 } else {
1780 return failmsg("Argument '%s' must be CvSeq, CvArr, or a sequence of numbers");
1781 }
1782}

1971
1972struct dims
1973{
1974 int count;
1975 int i[CV_MAX_DIM];
1976 int step[CV_MAX_DIM];
1977 int length[CV_MAX_DIM];
1978};
1979
1980static int convert_to_dim(PyObject *item, int i, dims *dst, CvArr *cva, const char *name = "no_name")
1981{
1982 if (!!PySlice_Check(item)) {
1983 Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slicelength;
1984 PySlice_GetIndicesEx((PySliceObject*)item, cvGetDimSize(cva, i), &start, &stop, &step, &slicelength);
1985 dst->i[i] = (int)start;
1986 dst->step[i] = (int)step;
1987 dst->length[i] = (int)slicelength;
1988 } else {
1989 int index = PyInt_AsLong(item);
1990 if (0 <= index)
1991 dst->i[i] = index;
1992 else
1993 dst->i[i] = cvGetDimSize(cva, i) + index;
1994 dst->step[i] = 0;
1995 dst->length[i] = 1;
1996 }
1997 return 1;
1998}
1999
2000static int convert_to_dims(PyObject *o, dims *dst, CvArr *cva, const char *name = "no_name")
2001{
2002 if (!PyTuple_Check(o)) {
2003 dst->count = 1;
2004 return convert_to_dim(o, 0, dst, cva, name);
2005 } else {
2006 PyObject *fi = PySequence_Fast(o, name);
2007 if (fi == NULL) {
2008 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "Expected tuple for index");
2009 return 0;
2010 }
2011 dst->count = (int)PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi);
2012 for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi); i++) {
2013 if (i >= cvGetDims(cva)) {
2014 return failmsg("Access specifies %d dimensions, but array only has %d", PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi), cvGetDims(cva));
2015 }
2016 PyObject *item = PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(fi, i);
2017 if (!convert_to_dim(item, (int)i, dst, cva, name))
2018 return 0;
2019 }
2020 Py_DECREF(fi);
2021 return 1;
2022 }
2023}

2179static PyObject *pythonize_CvMat(cvmat_t *m)
2180{
2181 // Need to make this CvMat look like any other, with a Python
2182 // buffer object as its data.
2183 CvMat *mat = m->a;
2184 assert(mat->step != 0);
2185#if 0
2186 PyObject *data = PyString_FromStringAndSize((char*)(mat->data.ptr), mat->rows * mat->step);
2187#else
2188 memtrack_t *o = PyObject_NEW(memtrack_t, &memtrack_Type);
2189 size_t gap = mat->data.ptr - (uchar*)mat->refcount;
2190 o->ptr = mat->refcount;
2191 o->owner = __LINE__;
2192 o->freeptr = true;
2193 o->size = gap + mat->rows * mat->step;
2194 o->backing = NULL;
2195 o->backingmat = NULL;
2196 PyObject *data = PyBuffer_FromReadWriteObject((PyObject*)o, (size_t)gap, mat->rows * mat->step);
2197 if (data == NULL)
2198 return NULL;
2199#endif
2200 m->data = data;
2201 m->offset = 0;
2202 Py_DECREF(o);
2203
2204 // Now m has a reference to data, which has a reference to o.
2205
2206 return (PyObject*)m;
2207}

2209static PyObject *pythonize_IplImage(iplimage_t *cva)
2210{
2211 // Need to make this iplimage look like any other, with a Python
2212 // string as its data.
2213 // So copy the image data into a Python string object, then release
2214 // it.
2215
2216 IplImage *ipl = (IplImage*)(cva->a);
2217 // PyObject *data = PyString_FromStringAndSize(ipl->imageData, ipl->imageSize);
2218
2219 memtrack_t *o = PyObject_NEW(memtrack_t, &memtrack_Type);
2220 assert(ipl->imageDataOrigin == ipl->imageData);
2221 o->ptr = ipl->imageDataOrigin;
2222 o->owner = __LINE__;
2223 o->freeptr = true;
2224 o->size = ipl->height * ipl->widthStep;
2225 o->backing = NULL;
2226 o->backingmat = NULL;
2227 PyObject *data = PyBuffer_FromReadWriteObject((PyObject*)o, (size_t)0, o->size);
2228 if (data == NULL)
2229 return NULL;
2230 Py_DECREF(o);
2231 cva->data = data;
2232 cva->offset = 0;
2233
2234 return (PyObject*)cva;
2235}

2552static PyObject *FROM_generic(generic r)
2553{
2554 if (r == NULL) {
2555 failmsg("OpenCV returned NULL");
2556 return NULL;
2557 }
2558 CvTypeInfo* t = cvTypeOf(r);
2559 if (strcmp(t->type_name, "opencv-image") == 0)
2560 return FROM_IplImagePTR((IplImage*)r);
2561 else if (strcmp(t->type_name, "opencv-matrix") == 0)
2562 return FROM_CvMat((CvMat*)r);
2563 else if (strcmp(t->type_name, "opencv-nd-matrix") == 0)
2564 return FROM_CvMatNDPTR((CvMatND*)r);
2565 else if (strcmp(t->type_name, "opencv-haar-classifier") == 0)

2774static PyObject *fromarray(PyObject *o, int allowND)
2775{
2776 PyObject *ao = PyObject_GetAttrString(o, "__array_struct__");
2777 PyObject *retval;
2778
2779 if ((ao == NULL) || !PyCObject_Check(ao)) {
2780 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "object does not have array interface");
2781 return NULL;
2782 }
2783 PyArrayInterface *pai = (PyArrayInterface*)PyCObject_AsVoidPtr(ao);
2784 if (pai->two != 2) {
2785 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "object does not have array interface");
2786 Py_DECREF(ao);
2787 return NULL;
2788 }
2789
2790 int type = -1;
2791
2792 switch (pai->typekind) {
2793 case 'i':
2794 if (pai->itemsize == 1)
2795 type = CV_8SC1;
2796 else if (pai->itemsize == 2)
2797 type = CV_16SC1;
2798 else if (pai->itemsize == 4)
2799 type = CV_32SC1;
2800 break;
2801
2802 case 'u':
2803 if (pai->itemsize == 1)
2804 type = CV_8UC1;
2805 else if (pai->itemsize == 2)
2806 type = CV_16UC1;
2807 break;
2808
2809 case 'f':
2810 if (pai->itemsize == 4)
2811 type = CV_32FC1;
2812 else if (pai->itemsize == 8)
2813 type = CV_64FC1;
2814 break;
2815
2816 }
2817 if (type == -1) {
2818 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "the array type is not supported by OpenCV");
2819 Py_DECREF(ao);
2820 return NULL;
2821 }
2822
2823 if (!allowND) {
2824 cvmat_t *m = PyObject_NEW(cvmat_t, &cvmat_Type);
2825 if (pai->nd == 2) {
2826 if (pai->strides[1] != pai->itemsize) {
2827 return failmsg("cv.fromarray array can only accept arrays with contiguous data"), (PyObject*)0;
2828 }
2829 ERRWRAP(m->a = cvCreateMatHeader((int)pai->shape[0], (int)pai->shape[1], type));
2830 m->a->step = (int)pai->strides[0];
2831 } else if (pai->nd == 3) {
2832 if (pai->shape[2] > CV_CN_MAX) {
2833 Py_DECREF(ao);
2834 return failmsg("cv.fromarray too many channels, see allowND argument"), (PyObject*)0;
2835 }
2836 ERRWRAP(m->a = cvCreateMatHeader((int)pai->shape[0], (int)pai->shape[1], type + ((int)(pai->shape[2] - 1) << CV_CN_SHIFT)));
2837 m->a->step = (int)pai->strides[0];
2838 } else {
2839 Py_DECREF(ao);
2840 return failmsg("cv.fromarray array can be 2D or 3D only, see allowND argument"), (PyObject*)0;
2841 }
2842 m->a->data.ptr = (uchar*)pai->data;
2843 //retval = pythonize_foreign_CvMat(m);
2844 m->data = o;
2845 m->offset = 0;
2846 retval = (PyObject*)m;
2847 } else {
2848 int dims[CV_MAX_DIM];
2849 int i;
2850 for (i = 0; i < pai->nd; i++)
2851 dims[i] = (int)pai->shape[i];
2852 cvmatnd_t *m = PyObject_NEW(cvmatnd_t, &cvmatnd_Type);
2853 ERRWRAP(m->a = cvCreateMatNDHeader(pai->nd, dims, type));
2854 m->a->data.ptr = (uchar*)pai->data;
2855 m->data = o;
2856 m->offset = 0;
2857 retval = (PyObject*)m;
2858 //retval = pythonize_CvMatND(m, ao);
2859 }
2860 Py_DECREF(ao);
2861 Py_INCREF(o);
2862 return retval;
2863}

2866class ranges {
2867public:
2868 Py_ssize_t len;
2869 float **rr;
2870 ranges() {
2871 len = 0;
2872 rr = NULL;
2873 }
2874 int fromobj(PyObject *o, const char *name = "no_name") {
2875 PyObject *fi = PySequence_Fast(o, name);
2876 if (fi == NULL)
2877 return 0;
2878 len = (int)PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi);
2879 rr = new float*[len];
2880 for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {
2881 PyObject *item = PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(fi, i);
2882 floats ff; ff.f = 0;
2883 if (!convert_to_floats(item, &ff))
2884 return 0;
2885 rr[i] = ff.f;
2886 }
2887 Py_DECREF(fi);
2888 return 1;
2889 }
2890 ~ranges() {
2891 for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < len; i++)
2892 delete rr[i];
2893 delete[] rr;
2894 }
2895};
2896
2897static int ranges_converter(PyObject *o, ranges* dst)
2898{
2899 return dst->fromobj(o);
2900}

2965// single index: return row
2966// 2 indices: row, column
2967// both row and column can be slices. column slice must have a step of 1.
2968//
2969// returns a scalar when all dimensions are specified and all are integers. Otherwise returns a CvMat.
2970//
2971static PyObject *cvarr_GetItem(PyObject *o, PyObject *key)
2972{
2973 dims dd;
2974
2975 CvArr *cva;
2976 if (!convert_to_CvArr(o, &cva, "src"))
2977 return NULL;
2978
2979 if (!convert_to_dims(key, &dd, cva, "key")) {
2980 return NULL;
2981 }
2982
2983 // Figure out if all supplied indices have a stride of zero - means they are not slices
2984 // and if all indices are positive
2985 int all0 = 1;
2986 for (int i = 0; i < dd.count; i++) {
2987 all0 &= (dd.step[i] == 0) && (0 <= dd.i[i]);
2988 }
2989
2990 // if every dimension supplied, and none are slices, return the scalar
2991 if ((cvGetDims(cva) == dd.count) && all0) {
2992 CvScalar s;
2993 ERRWRAP(s = cvGetND(cva, dd.i));
2994 return PyObject_FromCvScalar(s, cvGetElemType(cva));
2995 } else {
2996 // pad missing dimensions
2997 for (int i = dd.count; i < cvGetDims(cva); i++) {
2998 dd.i[i] = 0;
2999 dd.step[i] = 1;
3000 dd.length[i] = cvGetDimSize(cva, i);
3001 }
3002 dd.count = cvGetDims(cva);
3003
3004 // negative steps are illegal for OpenCV
3005 for (int i = 0; i < dd.count; i++) {
3006 if (dd.step[i] < 0)
3007 return failmsg("Negative step is illegal"), (PyObject*)0;
3008 }
3009
3010 // zero length illegal for OpenCV
3011 for (int i = 0; i < dd.count; i++) {
3012 if (dd.length[i] == 0)
3013 return failmsg("Zero sized dimension is illegal"), (PyObject*)0;
3014 }
3015
3016 // column step can only be 0 or 1
3017 if ((dd.step[dd.count-1] != 0) && (dd.step[dd.count-1] != 1))
3018 return failmsg("Column step is illegal"), (PyObject*)0;
3019
3020 if (is_cvmat(o) || is_iplimage(o)) {
3021 cvmat_t *sub = PyObject_NEW(cvmat_t, &cvmat_Type);
3022 sub->a = cvCreateMatHeader(dd.length[0], dd.length[1], cvGetElemType(cva));
3023 uchar *old0; // pointer to first element in old mat
3024 int oldstep;
3025 cvGetRawData(cva, &old0, &oldstep);
3026 uchar *new0; // pointer to first element in new mat
3027 ERRWRAP(new0 = cvPtrND(cva, dd.i));
3028
3029 sub->a->step = oldstep * dd.step[0];
3030 sub->data = what_data(o);
3031 Py_INCREF(sub->data);
3032 sub->offset = new0 - old0;
3033 return (PyObject*)sub;
3034 } else {
3035 cvmatnd_t *sub = PyObject_NEW(cvmatnd_t, &cvmatnd_Type);
3036 sub->a = cvCreateMatNDHeader(dd.count, dd.length, cvGetElemType(cva));
3037 uchar *old0; // pointer to first element in old mat
3038 cvGetRawData(cva, &old0);
3039 uchar *new0; // pointer to first element in new mat
3040 ERRWRAP(new0 = cvPtrND(cva, dd.i));
3041
3042 for (int d = 0; d < dd.count; d++) {
3043 int stp = dd.step[d];
3044 sub->a->dim[d].step = ((CvMatND*)cva)->dim[d].step * ((stp == 0) ? 1 : stp);
3045 sub->a->dim[d].size = dd.length[d];
3046 }
3047 sub->data = what_data(o);
3048 Py_INCREF(sub->data);
3049 sub->offset = new0 - old0;
3050 return (PyObject*)sub;
3051 }
3052 }
3053}
3054
3055static int cvarr_SetItem(PyObject *o, PyObject *key, PyObject *v)
3056{
3057 dims dd;
3058
3059 CvArr *cva;
3060 if (!convert_to_CvArr(o, &cva, "src"))
3061 return -1;
3062
3063 if (!convert_to_dims(key, &dd, cva, "key")) {
3064 return -1;
3065 }
3066
3067 if (cvGetDims(cva) != dd.count) {
3068 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "key length does not match array dimension");
3069 return -1;
3070 }
3071
3072 CvScalar s;
3073 if (PySequence_Check(v)) {
3074 PyObject *fi = PySequence_Fast(v, "v");
3075 if (fi == NULL)
3076 return -1;
3077 if (PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi) != CV_MAT_CN(cvGetElemType(cva))) {
3078 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "sequence size must be same as channel count");
3079 return -1;
3080 }
3081 for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < PySequence_Fast_GET_SIZE(fi); i++)
3082 s.val[i] = PyFloat_AsDouble(PySequence_Fast_GET_ITEM(fi, i));
3083 Py_DECREF(fi);
3084 } else {
3085 if (1 != CV_MAT_CN(cvGetElemType(cva))) {
3086 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "scalar supplied but channel count does not equal 1");
3087 return -1;
3088 }
3089 s.val[0] = PyFloat_AsDouble(v);
3090 }
3091 switch (dd.count) {
3092 case 1:
3093 ERRWRAPN(cvSet1D(cva, dd.i[0], s), -1);
3094 break;
3095 case 2:
3096 ERRWRAPN(cvSet2D(cva, dd.i[0], dd.i[1], s), -1);
3097 break;
3098 case 3:
3099 ERRWRAPN(cvSet3D(cva, dd.i[0], dd.i[1], dd.i[2], s), -1);
3100 break;
3101 default:
3102 ERRWRAPN(cvSetND(cva, dd.i, s), -1);
3103 // XXX - OpenCV bug? - seems as if an error in cvSetND does not set error status?
3104 break;
3105 }
3106 if (cvGetErrStatus() != 0) {
3107 translate_error_to_exception();
3108 return -1;
3109 }
3110
3111 return 0;
3112}

3164static PyObject *pycvCreateData(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
3165{
3166 PyObject *o;
3167
3168 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "O", &o))
3169 return NULL;
3170
3171 CvArr *a;
3172 if (!convert_to_CvArr(o, &a, "arr"))
3173 return NULL;
3174 ERRWRAP(cvCreateData(a));
3175
3176 Py_DECREF(what_data(o));
3177 if (is_iplimage(o)) {
3178 iplimage_t *ipl = (iplimage_t*)o;
3179 pythonize_IplImage(ipl);
3180 } else if (is_cvmat(o)) {
3181 cvmat_t *m = (cvmat_t*)o;
3182 pythonize_CvMat(m);

3740 return Py_BuildValue("dddddd", r[0], r[1], r[2], r[3], r[4], r[5]);
3741}

3743static PyObject *pycvGetMinMaxHistValue(PyObject *self, PyObject *args)
3744{
3745 CvHistogram* hist;
3746 PyObject *pyobj_hist = NULL;
3747 float min_val;
3748 float max_val;
3749 int min_loc[CV_MAX_DIM];
3750 int max_loc[CV_MAX_DIM];
3751
3752 if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "O", &pyobj_hist))
3753 return NULL;
3754 if (!convert_to_CvHistogram(pyobj_hist, &hist, "hist")) return NULL;
3755 ERRWRAP(cvGetMinMaxHistValue(hist, &min_val, &max_val, min_loc, max_loc));
3756 int d = cvGetDims(hist->bins);
3757 PyObject *pminloc = PyTuple_New(d), *pmaxloc = PyTuple_New(d);
3758 for (int i = 0; i < d; i++) {
3759 PyTuple_SetItem(pminloc, i, PyInt_FromLong(min_loc[i]));
3760 PyTuple_SetItem(pmaxloc, i, PyInt_FromLong(max_loc[i]));
3761 }
3762 return Py_BuildValue("ffNN", min_val, max_val, pminloc, pmaxloc);
3763}

3765static CvSeq* cvHOGDetectMultiScale( const CvArr* image, CvMemStorage* storage,
3766 const CvArr* svm_classifier=NULL, CvSize win_stride=cvSize(0,0),
3767 double hit_threshold=0, double scale=1.05,
3768 int group_threshold=2, CvSize padding=cvSize(0,0),
3769 CvSize win_size=cvSize(64,128), CvSize block_size=cvSize(16,16),
3770 CvSize block_stride=cvSize(8,8), CvSize cell_size=cvSize(8,8),
3771 int nbins=9, int gammaCorrection=1 )
3772{
3773 cv::HOGDescriptor hog(win_size, block_size, block_stride, cell_size, nbins, 1, -1, cv::HOGDescriptor::L2Hys, 0.2, gammaCorrection!=0);
3774 if(win_stride.width == 0 && win_stride.height == 0)
3775 win_stride = block_stride;
3776 cv::Mat img = cv::cvarrToMat(image);
3777 std::vector<cv::Rect> found;
3778 if(svm_classifier)
3779 {
3780 CvMat stub, *m = cvGetMat(svm_classifier, &stub);
3781 int sz = m->cols*m->rows;
3782 CV_Assert(CV_IS_MAT_CONT(m->type) && (m->cols == 1 || m->rows == 1) && CV_MAT_TYPE(m->type) == CV_32FC1);
3783 std::vector<float> w(sz);
3784 std::copy(m->data.fl, m->data.fl + sz, w.begin());
3785 hog.setSVMDetector(w);
3786 }
3787 else
3788 hog.setSVMDetector(cv::HOGDescriptor::getDefaultPeopleDetector());
3789 hog.detectMultiScale(img, found, hit_threshold, win_stride, padding, scale, group_threshold);
3790 CvSeq* seq = cvCreateSeq(cv::DataType<cv::Rect>::type, sizeof(CvSeq), sizeof(cv::Rect), storage);
3791 if(found.size())
3792 cvSeqPushMulti(seq, &found[0], (int)found.size());
3793 return seq;
3794}

3842static double cppKMeans(const CvArr* _samples, int cluster_count, CvArr* _labels,
3843 CvTermCriteria termcrit, int attempts, int flags, CvArr* _centers)

3852 flags, _centers ? cv::_OutputArray(centers) : cv::_OutputArray() );
3853}
